caption: I just loved their food. I always get awesome service here. The place is neat and the employees are always super friendly. Highly recommended.

This is our neighborhood spot, sorta hole-in-the-wall looking. LOVE the food though—flavors are on point, portions are huge, and everyone is very friendly. Highly recommend if you’re looking for quick, tasty Chinese food.

Have to admit that as neighbors, we've overlooked this tiny restaurant, which offers takeout but has no place to sit indoors -- just a few seats on the wide sidewalk outside.  (Truth be told, we kind of assumed it mainly served tourists.)  But all we get these days is takeout and this evening we were craving Chinese food -- the sort we could find easily in Southern California, not the Asian-fusion dishes you get so often in DC (which to us are more like Thai and Vietnamese.)  After reading some positive reviews and finding out that it was indeed open (despite the fact that Woodley Park's two big hotels have been closed for months), we decided to give Eddie's Cafe a try.  We're SO glad we did and are just sorry it took us so long!  Each dish was prepared in a different style, with different sauces and flavors; the portions were large; and it tasted really good.  (Kung Pao Chicken, Eggplant with Ginger & Basil Sauce, and Pan Fried String Beans.)  And we've got soup saved for tomorrow to enjoy with the leftovers.  This is actually the best Chinese food we've found in this neighborhood, and we plan to become regulars.  Don't ignore what seem to be holes-in-the wall!
One of the better Chinese foods of DC

This is my favorite casual Chinese delivery in DC. Can’t wait for them to open again. Best dishes include their steamed vegetable dumplings, hunan shrimp, diet dishes with choice of sauce, and sesame chicken.
Excellent Chinese food! Very nice staff!

Got takeout last night. First time here, first time to DC, asked fellow patrons what they ordered. And got in-depth high recommendations on the Mongolian Beef, Kung Pao chicken, and eggplant with basil and ginger-- the latter a dish they always order. I ordered these dishes myself and it was delicious. Chicken was spicy with loads of peanuts. Eggplant well-cooked, not too oily. White rice was PERFECT, fluffy, and fresh. I can't wait to come back again during my visit.

Great Chinese delivery in NW. Kung Pao chicken, General Tsos (all options, even shrimp), Orange Beef, Drunken noodle, all the soups and steamed dumplings are our go-tos. Everything else in my opinion is sub par. The wife and I have been ordering from Eddy's Cafe since 2005. She even wanted to cancel our date and order from here the night I proposed to her!
Eddie's is that place you go for reliable cheap Chinese food and I am HERE FOR IT.

When it comes to Chinese carry outs, you really only need to eat at any given place once to know if it's any good or not. This joint takes the mark in it having quality food for a fair price. I got general tso chicken and the chicken was nice and tender with a very good flavor of sauce. This is another hole in the wall joint, with no indoor seating but does have outdoor. You can also get the Old Town Trolley tickets here, which is useful. I certainly don't have a need for that but it's worth mentioning for those who are. Outside of that, there's nothing more than that to say. Well worth it.

I like to go with friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I go their often. This recommendation is always successful. The the food there is yummy and the team is efficient and cooperative. always when we go to this place we enjoy a delightful evening.  I recommend this place with pleasure.

My boyfriend and I ordered orange chicken, lo mein, dumplings, and a side of white rice for delivery at a nearby hotel that was hosting a convention (on Halloween, on a Saturday night). Our food was not only delivered earlier than we expected via a pleasant delivery man, but it was hot, fresh, and absolutely delicious to boot. Great prices as well. We will definitely order from Eddie's again the next time we're in DC. Highly recommend!

i've had much better for much cheaper but i suppose nothing is all that cheap in dc.  the online order is very efficient and arrived very promptly with an extremely friendly carrier. you might want to ask for utensils. kind of hard to eat soup and rice with your hands.  the food tastes like they use fresh, clean ingredients however i must be spoiled because i was somewhat disappointed by the portion sizes (wanton soup with 2 mediocre wantons in it....nothing special) if you like vegetable spring rolls, those are good here. if you prefer plain fried rice, that's what you get with a combo. bean curd is alright, i've had much worse. the photo online of their tempura shrimp is a total joke. it is basically four 2" nuggets of sweet and sour shrimp on a bed of soggy cellophane noodles. if that's considered tempura, i'm afraid to know what their sweet and sour shrimp is. i guess there could be more agonizing deaths to $6. out of my wallet but if  i wanted bait, i would have ordered bait. the sauce that came with the shrimp was some sort of thin, citrus zest sauce that assaulted my palette to the point of spitting. not a fan of that sauce but again a matter of taste. giving three stars rather than 2 because a. the delivery man was wonderful and b. the spring rolls were fresh and clean.
